      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(irc): chunk PRIVMSG on UTF-16 boundary to avoid lone surrogates",
        "body": "## Problem\n`sendPrivmsg` splits long messages with `chunk.slice(0, splitAt)` on UTF-16 code units. An emoji that straddles the chunk boundary gets cut into a lone surrogate, so the recipient sees a replacement character.\n\n## Fix\nSplit on code-point boundaries so multi-unit characters are never broken across chunks.\n\n## Proof\nAdded `extensions/irc/src/client.surrogate.test.ts` with a fake socket asserting no emitted PRIVMSG line contains a lone surrogate — fails before, passes after. No live IRC connection.\n",
